        "required": false,
        "shortDescription": "<p> The number of times to retry a failed batch of records.</p>\n",
        "longDescription": "<div class=\"highlight-wrapper\">\n  <div style=\"margin-right: 16px;line-height: 0px;\">\n  <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"#ED8B00\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\">\n    <path d=\"M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z\"></path>\n    <line x1=\"12\" y1=\"9\" x2=\"12\" y2=\"13\"></line>\n    <line x1=\"12\" y1=\"17\" x2=\"12.01\" y2=\"17\"></line>\n  </svg>\n  </div>\n  <div><p><strong>Important:</strong> If an error occurs, the entire batch is retried, including records that were processed successfully. Your function should be idempotent to handle this.</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
        "typeInfo": {
          "kind": "primitive",
          "types": [
            "number"
          ]
        }
